messages.content: ComfyUI_pose_inter generates transition frames between two character posture images.
What is the prerequisite for running ComfyUI_pose_inter?
The prerequisite for running ComfyUI_pose_inter is to have installed comfyui_controlnet_aux, specifically using its Open Pose or DWPose preprocessor.
What are the input requirements for ComfyUI_pose_inter?
The input requirements for ComfyUI_pose_inter are two character posture images.
What is the output of ComfyUI_pose_inter?
The output of ComfyUI_pose_inter is transition frames between the two input character posture images.
How can ComfyUI_pose_inter be improved for character posture image processing?
ComfyUI_pose_inter could be improved by integrating more sophisticated preprocessing methods and improving the accuracy of the generated transition frames.

The text does not specifically mention whether ComfyUI_pose_inter can handle non-human characters, but it is implied from the context that it is designed for generating transitions between character postures.
What kind of applications can be made using ComfyUI_pose_inter?
Applications for generating animated transitions or character postures in games, animations, or any other visual media where realistic and smooth character movements are important.
